 "paths": ["Compromise admin → Set malicious oracle → Manipulate prices → Exploit"]}, {"id": "F-007", "severity": "High", "confidence": "medium", "title": "Unchecked Approval Race Condition in checkTransferIn", "locations": ["Contract.sol:372-385"], "claim": "checkTransferIn performs allowance and balance checks separately. Between check and actual transfer, another transaction could decrease allowance/balance (ERC20 race condition).", "impact": "If user has low balance/allowance, attacker could potentially grief their supply/borrow transactions by front-running with another transaction that reduces their allowance.", "paths": ["User approves → Attacker front-runs with lower allowance → User tx fails"]}, {"id": "F-008", "severity": "High", "confidence": "medium", "title": "Self-Liquidation Without Collateral Loss", "locations": ["Contract.sol:2139-2391"], "claim": "liquidateBorrow doesn't check that liquidator != targetAccount. A user can liquidate themselves to get discount on their own collateral.", "impact": "User can liquidate their own position to effectively get a discount on their collateral (liquidation discount) without any penalty, extracting value from the protocol and other users.", "paths": ["Borrow → Become underwater → Call liquidateBorrow on self → Get discount"]}, {"id": "F-009", "severity": "Medium", "confidence": "high", "title": "No Timelock on Critical Parameter Changes", "locations": ["Contract.sol:1344-1431"], "claim": "Admin can change collateral ratio, liquidation discount, and origination fee immediately without any delay.", "impact": "Admin could maliciously change parameters to liquidate users, steal collateral, or break protocol functionality. Users have no time to react to parameter changes.", "paths": ["Admin changes collateral ratio to 1.0 → All users become underwater → Liquidate everyone"]}, {"id": "F-010", "severity": "Medium", "confidence": "medium", "title": "Unsupported Market Still Counts as Collateral", "locations": ["Contract.sol:1315-1335", "Contract.sol:1827-1900"], "locations": ["Contract.sol:1315-1335", "Contract.sol:1827-1900"], "claim": "When market is suspended via _suspendMarket, existing collateral balances still count for liquidity calculations. Users can withdraw/supply/borrow using suspended markets as collateral.", "impact": "Admin can suspend a market (e.g., due to price oracle failure) but borrowers using that asset as collateral remain operational. The collateral becomes worthless but protocol still considers it valuable, leading to insolvency.", "paths": ["Market becomes worthless → Admin suspends → But collateral still counts → Protocol undercollateralized"]}, {"id": "F-011", "severity": "Medium", "confidence": "medium", "title": "No Maximum Borrow Amount Check", "locations": ["Contract.sol:2548-2669"], "claim": "The borrow function checks account liquidity but doesn't enforce a maximum borrow amount per user or per market.", "impact": "A single user can borrow the entire protocol's liquidity in one asset, causing potential DoS for other borrowers and concentrating risk.", "paths": ["User borrows max → Other users cannot borrow → Protocol effectively locks"]}, {"id": "F-012", "severity": "Low", "confidence": "high", "title": "Inconsistent Error Handling Between doTransferIn and doTransferOut", "locations": ["Contract.sol:396-422", "Contract.sol:451-477"], "claim": "doTransferIn reverts on TOKEN_TRANSFER_FAILED but doTransferOut only returns error code without reverting in some code paths.", "impact": "Inconsistent behavior makes it difficult to predict protocol state after failed transfers. Could lead to accounting errors.", "paths": ["doTransferOut returns false → Returns error but continues execution"]}, {"id": "F-013", "severity": "Low", "confidence": "medium", "title": "Potential Storage Collision in collateralMarkets Array", "locations": ["Contract.sol:898-906", "Contract.sol:1840"], "claim": "addCollateralMarket doesn't verify if market is properly supported before adding. If a market is re-supported after suspension, duplicate entries could exist.", "impact": "Duplicate entries in collateralMarkets lead to double-counting of collateral in liquidity calculations.", "paths": ["Suspend market → Support again → Duplicate in array → Liquidity calculation wrong"]}, {"id": "F-014", "severity": "Informational", "confidence": "high", "title": "Solidity Version 0.4.24 Has Known Vulnerabilities", "locations": ["Contract.sol:1"], "claim": "Contract uses solidity ^0.4.24 which has known vulnerabilities like transaction ordering dependence and integer overflow bugs in earlier versions.", "impact": "While CarefulMath provides overflow protection, the underlying EVM may have other related issues in this compiler version.", "paths": []}, {"id": "F-015", "severity": "Informational", "confidence": "medium", "title": "No Event Emissions for Some State Changes", "locations": ["Contract.sol:744-746"], "claim": "The collateralMarkets array is modified without emitting any event.", "impact": "Off-chain monitoring and indexing becomes difficult. Historical record of collateral market changes is incomplete.", "paths": []}]
